---

## Example: Value Investing Rules

### Investment Philosophy
- Focus on companies with consistent FCF generation over 5+ years
- Avoid companies with D/E ratio > 1.5 (financial companies excluded)
- Look for businesses with sustainable competitive advantages (経済的堀)

### Screening Criteria
- ROE > 10% for 3 consecutive years
- PBR < 1.5 (deep value) or PBR < 3.0 with high ROE
- Dividend yield > 2% preferred
- Market cap > ¥50B for liquidity

### Red Flags
- Revenue declining for 2+ consecutive years
- Goodwill > 30% of total assets
- Management compensation growing faster than earnings

---

## How to Use

Create `.dexter/RULES.md` with your own rules:

```bash
mkdir -p .dexter
cp RULES.md.example .dexter/RULES.md
# Then edit .dexter/RULES.md to your preferences
```

Rules are loaded automatically on startup and displayed with `/rules`.
